S3-T03: internal/ratelimit — Redis sliding window rate limiter with Lua script
Completed: 2026-04-05

## Deliverables

1. internal/ratelimit/ratelimit.go — RedisLimiter with embedded Lua script (EVALSHA via redis.NewScript)
2. internal/ratelimit/config.go — Tier definitions (AnonymousRedirect, AnonymousCreate, FreeCreate, ProCreate, PasswordAttempt)
3. internal/ratelimit/middleware.go — SetRateLimitHeaders helper for X-RateLimit-* and Retry-After headers
4. internal/ratelimit/ratelimit_test.go — 11 tests covering all required scenarios

## Test Results

All 11 tests PASS with -race:
- TestAllowUnderLimit
- TestDenyAtLimit
- TestSlidingWindowExpiry (injectable clock)
- TestResultFieldsCorrect
- TestIndependentKeys
- TestFailOpenWhenRedisUnavailable
- TestFailClosedWhenRedisUnavailable
- TestConcurrentRequests (20 goroutines, verifies Lua atomicity)
- TestSetRateLimitHeaders (allowed + denied)
- TestSetRateLimitHeadersHTTP429
- TestTierValues

## Design Decisions

- Clock is injectable via WithClock option (func() time.Time) for deterministic testing
- FailurePolicy (FailOpen/FailClosed) is configurable per limiter instance
- Lua script uses sorted set with unique request IDs (timestamp:uuid) as members, millisecond timestamps as scores
- Script registered via redis.NewScript for automatic EVALSHA optimization
- Scripter interface accepts redis.Scripter for testability
